STEP 3C — MEMORY BOUNDARY RULES
Append to CLAUDE.md:

## Memory Rules

### claude-mem — Session Working Memory (Claude Code only)
Write to claude-mem:
- What happened this session
- Code patterns discovered in this codebase
- Errors encountered and how they were fixed
- File locations of important logic
Do NOT write to claude-mem:
- High-level architectural decisions → goes to CONTEXT.md
- Long-term project evolution → goes to Hermes
- Cross-week patterns → goes to Hermes

### Hermes — Project Lifecycle Memory (background agent)
Write to Hermes memory:
- Architectural decisions and why they were made
- Patterns that repeat across multiple sessions
- Project evolution and milestone notes
- Anything that needs to be remembered in 2 weeks
Do NOT write to Hermes:
- What happened today → goes to claude-mem + session-notes
- File-level implementation details → goes to claude-mem

### session-notes.md — The Bridge (size-bounded)
At the end of each session:
1. Summarise session into session-notes.md
2. Short-term detail → claude-mem
3. Long-term decisions → Hermes memory
Decision rule: "Will I need this in 2 weeks?" Yes → Hermes. No → claude-mem.
Never write the same memory to both claude-mem and Hermes.

Size rules — enforced every session end:
- session-notes.md maximum: 50 lines total
- When it exceeds 50 lines: archive completed items to
  docs/archive/session-YYYY-MM-DD.md and reset the file
- Only keep in the live file at all times:
  Active Tasks (all) + last 3 Decisions + last 3 Known Issues
- This prevents startup context injection from growing unbounded
  across weeks of use — the file stays permanently small

### General Memory Rules
- Session start: read .claude/session-notes.md and CONTEXT.md before anything else
- After every completed task: update .claude/session-notes.md
- New domain term discovered: add to CONTEXT.md immediately
- Architectural decision made: add to CONTEXT.md under Key Decisions
- Session end: write a one-paragraph summary at the top of session-notes.md
- If session-notes.md exceeds 50 lines: archive before ending the session

